{
  "page": "House Toyne",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">House Toyne</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Toyne.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Toyne.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/27/House_Toyne.svg/250px-House_Toyne.svg.png\" width=\"250\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/27/House_Toyne.svg/375px-House_Toyne.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/27/House_Toyne.svg/500px-House_Toyne.svg.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"width:100%;min-width:300px;position:relative;z-index:100;border:0 grey solid;margin-top:-3em;margin-bottom:1em;\"><div style=\"display: table; width: calc(100% - 80px); height: 28px; font-size: 12px; line-height: 12px; margin: 0px auto 0px; padding: 0;border:0; position: relative; border-collapse:collapse; text-align: center; font-family: &#39;Uncial Antiqua&#39;; color: #000; background: linear-gradient(90deg, #333 0%, #333 10%, #ea0 10%, #ea0 90%, #333 90%);\">\n  <div style=\"display:table-cell; vertical-align: middle; padding: 4px; clip-path: polygon(2px 2px, calc(100% - 2px) 2px, calc(100% - 2px) calc(100% - 2px), 2px calc(100% - 2px)); background: linear-gradient(90deg, #000 0%, #000 10%, #fd0 10%, #fd0 90%, #000 90%);\">Fly High, Fly Far</div>\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top: -14px; width: 56px; height: 28px; z-index: -3; left: -42px; clip-path: polygon(calc(100% - 2px) calc(100% - 2px), 5px calc(100% - 2px), calc(25% + 3px) 50%, 5px 2px, calc(100% - 2px) 2px, 75% 50%, calc(100% - 2px) calc(100% - 2px), calc(100% - 2px) 5px, calc(75% + 3px) 50%); background: #000;\"></div>\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top: -14px; width: 56px; height: 28px; z-index: -4; left: -42px; clip-path: polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 100% 100%, 0% 100%, 25% 50%); background: #333;\"></div>\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top: -14px; width: 56px; height: 28px; z-index: -3; right: -42px; clip-path: polygon(2px calc(100% - 2px), calc(100% - 5px) calc(100% - 2px), calc(75% - 3px) 50%, calc(100% - 5px) 2px, 2px 2px, 25% 50%, 2px calc(100% - 2px), 2px 5px, calc(25% - 3px) 50%); background: #000;\"></div>\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top: -14px; width: 56px; height: 28px; z-index: -4; right: -42px; clip-path: polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 75% 50%, 100% 100%, 0% 100%); background: #333;\"></div></div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Coat of arms</th><td>\nA winged heart, black on gold, within a black bordure embattled<br />(<i>Or, a heart with wings within a bordure embattled sable</i>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Head</th><td>\nExtinct</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Region</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">Stormlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Overlord</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon\" title=\"House Baratheon\">House Baratheon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died out</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/281_AC\" title=\"281 AC\">281&#160;AC</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_296_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">296&#160;AC</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>House Toyne</b> is an extinct noble house from the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>. According to semi-canon sources, they blazoned their arms with a winged heart, black on gold, within a black bordure embattled.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Citadel_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Citadel-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Their words are \"Fly High, Fly Far\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Historical_Toynes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Historical Toynes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Toyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Terrence_Toyne\" title=\"Terrence Toyne\">Terrence Toyne</a> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> who fell in love with <a href=\"/index.php/Bethany_Bracken\" title=\"Bethany Bracken\">Bethany Bracken</a>, a mistress of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_178_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">178&#160;AC</a>, the king found them abed, and had Terrence executed by being dismembered piece by piece, which Bethany was forced to watch before she was also executed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Terrence's <a href=\"/index.php/Brothers_Toyne\" title=\"Brothers Toyne\">two brothers</a> sought vengeance against the king, but he was defended by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Viserys_II)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Viserys II)\">Aemon the Dragonknight</a>, also of the Kingsguard, who slew the brothers but was likewise killed by them. These series of actions led to the downfall of House Toyne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Toyne\" title=\"Simon Toyne\">Simon Toyne</a> was the leader of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood_Brotherhood\" title=\"Kingswood Brotherhood\">Kingswood Brotherhood</a>, an <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlaw\">outlaw</a> band that became such a nuisance that in <a href=\"/index.php/281_AC\" title=\"281 AC\">281&#160;AC</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a> sent a detachment of soldiers led by notable members of the Kingsguard to destroy them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a> killed Simon while rescuing Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Swann\" title=\"Jeyne Swann\">Jeyne Swann</a> and her <a href=\"/index.php/Septa\" title=\"Septa\">septa</a> from the Brotherhood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Barristan also recalled that Simon attended <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Steffon%27s_tourney\" title=\"Lord Steffon&#39;s tourney\">Lord Steffon's tourney</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> as a <a href=\"/index.php/Mystery_knight\" title=\"Mystery knight\">mystery knight</a> who was defeated by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaegar Targaryen\">Rhaegar Targaryen</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> though, according to a semi-canon source, Barristan may have confused two separate tourneys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The last known member of the family was Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Myles_Toyne\" title=\"Myles Toyne\">Myles Toyne</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Captain-general\" title=\"Captain-general\">captain-general</a> of the exiled <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Historical_Toynes\">Historical Toynes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Toyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Historical Toynes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Historical members of House Toyne include:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Terrence_Toyne\" title=\"Terrence Toyne\">Terrence Toyne</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>.</li>\n<li>Terrence's <a href=\"/index.php/Brothers_Toyne\" title=\"Brothers Toyne\">two brothers</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Toyne\" title=\"Simon Toyne\">Simon Toyne</a>, the leader of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood_Brotherhood\" title=\"Kingswood Brotherhood\">Kingswood Brotherhood</a>.</li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Myles_Toyne\" title=\"Myles Toyne\">Myles Toyne</a>, called Blackheart, a captain-general of the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a>.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Toyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Terrence_Toyne\" title=\"Terrence Toyne\">Terrence Toyne</a> was found abed with <a href=\"/index.php/Bethany_Bracken\" title=\"Bethany Bracken\">his king's mistress</a>. 'Twas love, he swore, but it cost his life and hers, and brought about the downfall of his House and the death of <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Viserys_II)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Viserys II)\">the noblest knight who ever lived</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Arys_Oakheart\" title=\"Arys Oakheart\">Arys Oakheart</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Toyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Citadel-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Citadel_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Citadel. Heraldry: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.westeros.org/Citadel/Heraldry/Houses/8/\">Houses in the Stormlands</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Citadel. <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.westeros.org/Citadel/Heraldry/Mottoes/\">House Mottoes</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_13\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 13\">Chapter 13</a>, The Soiled Knight.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_17\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 17\">Chapter 17</a>, Cersei IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_30\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 30\">Chapter 30</a>, Jon IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_67\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 67\">Chapter 67</a>, Jaime VIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_42\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 42\">Chapter 42</a>, Daenerys IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=